    • Method Detail

      • fromFile

        static ProteinFastaFileDataStore fromFile(File fasta)
                                   throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: ProteinFastaDataStore
        Create a ProteinFastaDataStore of all the records in the given fasta file. Warning! This usually stores all the records in memory use ProteinFastaDataStore.fromFile(File, DataStoreProviderHint) or ProteinFastaFileDataStoreBuilder to handle the file or datastore implementation differently.
        Specified by:
        fromFile in interface ProteinFastaDataStore
        Parameters:
        fasta - the fasta file make a ProteinFastaDataStore with; can not be null and must exist.
        Returns:
        a new ProteinFastaDataStore; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the fasta file does not exist, or can not be read.
        See Also:
        ProteinFastaFileDataStoreBuilder, ProteinFastaDataStore.fromFile(File, DataStoreProviderHint)
